sues in the light of a series of guest lectures from scholars of religion law sociology cultural studies education and social justice and will aim to help students draw connections between religion and non belief and one's role as a global citizen wednesdays starting january 11 12 00 pm arrillaga dining commons study room these lectures are open to the public speaker schedule unit 1 the ethics of the stranger in various religious traditions january 11 bob gregg the stranger in jewish christian and islamic tradition january 18 steve weitzman the genesis of hospitality january 25 linda hess february 1 senator russ feingold and sister rabbi dena feingold february 8 discussion day unit 2 the ethics of the stranger in contemporary society the case of immigration february 15 tomas jimenez sociology of immigration february 22 discussion day february 29 12 15 jayashri srikantiah immigration and the law march 7 ramon saldivar cultural studies approach to immigration march 14 conclusion mini presentations search search for directions get directions giving to orl please click here show your support to the orl office for religious life stanford university memorial church 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 2090 650 723 1762
